sub_title: English Language Learning teacher at UWC Maastricht
summary:
As an English Language Teacher to beginner to intermediate speakers of English at UWC Maastricht, I teach academic language (CALP), academic skills and Basic Interpersonal Communication Skills (BICS). My lessons are student centered and designed according to the communicative approach and CLIL. I teach English while focusing my lessons on preparing students for their futures and working with applications (Zotero, Google Workspace) that allow them to engage fully and effectively with their IB subjects. 

The path that has brought me here, allows me to assist students to deepen their intercultural communicative competence and develop the critical and interdisciplinary thinking required to succeed in the IB. The foundations that I draw from are my time at UWCSEA (2014) and the double bachelor's degree (2018) in liberal arts at the University College Maastricht and the University College Freiburg, with an exchange semester at the University of California Davis. As well as, the honours track "U-teach" of the masters program "English Language and Culture: Communication and Education" (2021). I owe a large thanks to the educators, intership supervisors, and program of U-teach, as they allowed me to explore and fall in love with international schooling, multilingualism, translanguaging and immersive language learning environments.

Over the course of my university education I have acquired skills in intercultural communicative competence, curriculum development, research, and teaching English as a second language, and as the IB language and literature course. I also explored work and volunteering as a private Dutch and English tutor as well as English oral exam assessor.
